# **ğŸ“Œ DSA & Sorting + Arrays Cheat Sheet (1 Page)**

**Note:** All code in Java, concise and ready to write.

---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ **Linear Search**

```java
int linearSearch(int[] arr, int target){
    for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++)
        if(arr[i]==target) return i;
    return -1;
}
```

* **Concept:** Check elements one by one
* **Time:** O(n), **Space:** O(1)
* **Edge:** empty array, single element, not found

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ **Binary Search (Iterative)**

```java
int binarySearch(int[] arr,int target){
    int low=0,high=arr.length-1;
    while(low<=high){
        int mid=low+(high-low)/2;
        if(arr[mid]==target) return mid;
        else if(target<arr[mid]) high=mid-1;
        else low=mid+1;
    }
    return -1;
}
```

* **Concept:** Divide & conquer, sorted array
* **Time:** O(log n), **Space:** O(1)
* **Edge:** empty array, duplicates

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ **Bubble Sort**

```java
void bubbleSort(int[] arr){
    int n=arr.length; boolean swapped;
    for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
        swapped=false;
        for(int j=0;j<n-i-1;j++)
            if(arr[j]>arr[j+1]){
                int t=arr[j]; arr[j]=arr[j+1]; arr[j+1]=t; swapped=true;
            }
        if(!swapped) break;
    }
}
```

* **Best:** O(n), Worst: O(nÂ²), Stable âœ…
* **Edge:** empty/single/ already sorted

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ **Selection Sort**

```java
void selectionSort(int[] arr){
    int n=arr.length;
    for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
        int min=i;
        for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++) if(arr[j]<arr[min]) min=j;
        int t=arr[min]; arr[min]=arr[i]; arr[i]=t;
    }
}
```

* Always O(nÂ²), not stable âŒ
* **Edge:** duplicates, sorted

---

## 5ï¸âƒ£ **Insertion Sort**

```java
void insertionSort(int[] arr){
    for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++){
        int key=arr[i],j=i-1;
        while(j>=0 && arr[j]>key){ arr[j+1]=arr[j]; j--; }
        arr[j+1]=key;
    }
}
```

* **Best:** O(n) nearly sorted
* **Worst:** O(nÂ²) reverse sorted
* **Edge:** empty, single element

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ **Array Utilities**

**Reverse**

```java
void reverse(int[] arr){ int l=0,r=arr.length-1; while(l<r){int t=arr[l];arr[l]=arr[r];arr[r]=t;l++;r--;}}
```

**Max**

```java
int max(int[] arr){int m=arr[0]; for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++) if(arr[i]>m) m=arr[i]; return m;}
```

**Second Largest**

```java
int secondLargest(int[] arr){
    int first=Integer.MIN_VALUE,second=Integer.MIN_VALUE;
    for(int num:arr){
        if(num>first){second=first;first=num;}
        else if(num>second && num!=first) second=num;
    }
    return second;
}
```

**Is Sorted**

```java
boolean isSorted(int[] arr){for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++) if(arr[i]<arr[i-1]) return false; return true;}
```

**Remove Duplicates (Sorted Array)**

```java
int removeDup(int[] arr){
    if(arr.length==0) return 0;
    int j=0;
    for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++) if(arr[i]!=arr[j]) arr[++j]=arr[i];
    return j+1;
}
```

---

## 7ï¸âƒ£ **Important Edge Cases**

* Empty array / single element
* Already sorted / reverse sorted
* Duplicates / all same elements
* Negative numbers
* Index out of bounds

---

## 8ï¸âƒ£ **Complexity Quick Reference**

| Algo          | Best  | Worst    | Stable |
| ------------- | ----- | -------- | ------ |
| Linear Search | O(1)  | O(n)     | âœ…      |
| Binary Search | O(1)  | O(log n) | âœ…      |
| Bubble        | O(n)  | O(nÂ²)    | âœ…      |
| Selection     | O(nÂ²) | O(nÂ²)    | âŒ      |
| Insertion     | O(n)  | O(nÂ²)    | âœ…      |

